cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper discusses the use of expectation maximization (EM) as a message passing algorithm in factor graphs. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of message passing algorithms is often studied in the context of control systems (cs.SY) and data structures (cs.DS).
